		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">Memblers wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">And honestly, while I like my old Gameboy, the screen quality with all the blurring is total crap.</div>
<br />Older GB games and some GBC games are very good. Too many of the later GBC games were total crap. I guess people were not used to coding for 8-bit systems anymore.
<br />
<br />As for the console, the original was indeed very green and blurry. The pocket version was a little better, it was actually B&amp;W, but still a bit blurry. The GBC screen was pretty good, but you still have to play on a bright place to get decent contrast/colors. I still have my pocket and GBC. I think someday I'll buy a GBA, when it gets really cheap.
<br />
<br />IMO, the best games are in B&amp;W.

		

